HEADWORD: Frigatoon
<hw>Frig"a*toon`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>fregatone</ets>: cf. F.<ets>fr⟦eacute⟧gaton</ets>. See
<er>Frigate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A Venetian vessel, with
a square stern, having only a mainmast, jigger mast, and bowsprit; also
a sloop of war ship-rigged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

